README.RADSEC_SERVER_CLIENT_CA

This directory can contain multiple CA certificates, which are used
to validate client certificates the RadSec (RADIUS over TLS) clients
are using to connect to the RadSec server (TCP 2083).

You can copy an example CA certificate such as:

intermediate-CA-I1-crt.pem
intermediate-CA-I2-crt.pem
root-CA-crt.pem

from the previous directory to this directory to allow all certificates
validated by that CA or intermediate CAs under it to connect to this
server.

Or you can add your own root CA certificate to use it to verify client
certificates.

